      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey i was reading about hiit workouts and kept seeing stuff about lactic acid. can u explain how it actually gets made in the muscles and how the body gets rid of it after a set? thanks",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Lactic acid is a byproduct of anaerobic metabolism, which occurs when your muscles don't have enough oxygen to produce energy efficiently. It's produced when your body breaks down glucose to fuel high-intensity, short-duration activities like HIIT workouts. The process involves anaerobic glycolysis, where glucose is converted into lactate, and this occurs in the muscles' cytosol. The lactic acid is then transported through the bloodstream to the liver for metabolism and eventual excretion.",
